# Accessibility Standards

All components must meet **WCAG 2.1 Level AA** compliance. Carbon Design System provides a strong baseline — these rules extend and enforce it project-wide.

---

## 1. Color Contrast

### Text Contrast Ratios (WCAG 1.4.3 / 1.4.11)
- **Normal text** (< 18px or < 14px bold): minimum **4.5:1** contrast ratio
- **Large text** (≥ 18px or ≥ 14px bold): minimum **3:1** contrast ratio
- **UI components** (borders, icons, focus rings): minimum **3:1** contrast ratio

### Rules
- **NEVER** hardcode colors. Always use semantic tokens:
  ```scss
  color: var(--text-primary);          // main text
  color: var(--text-secondary);        // supporting text
  color: var(--text-on-color);         // text on colored backgrounds
  background: var(--background-primary);
  ```
- **NEVER** use dark text on dark backgrounds or light text on light backgrounds
- **ALWAYS** test in both light (`white`) and dark (`g100`) themes
- Use `--text-on-color` (always white) when text sits on `--interactive-primary` (brand red) or any colored background
- Check contrast with browser DevTools accessibility panel or https://webaim.org/resources/contrastchecker/

### Do / Don't

// ✅ DO - theme-aware, adapts to light and dark
.my-label { color: var(--text-primary); }

// ❌ DON'T - hardcoded, breaks dark mode
.my-label { color: #161616; }

// ✅ DO - white text on brand red
.badge { background: var(--interactive-primary); color: var(--text-on-color); }

// ❌ DON'T - primary text on colored background (dark in dark mode)
.badge { background: var(--interactive-primary); color: var(--text-primary); }
```

---

## 2. Keyboard Navigation (WCAG 2.1.1 / 2.4.3 / 2.4.7)

- **ALL interactive elements** must be reachable and operable via keyboard
- Tab order must follow the visual reading order (left-to-right, top-to-bottom)
- **NEVER** use `tabindex` values greater than 0 (breaks natural tab flow)
- `tabindex="0"` is allowed for custom interactive elements (e.g., custom tiles)
- `tabindex="-1"` is allowed for programmatic focus management only

### Focus Indicators
- **NEVER** use `outline: none` or `outline: 0` without providing a custom visible focus style
- Focus rings must have at least **3:1** contrast against adjacent colors
- Carbon provides built-in focus rings — do not override them unless replacing with a compliant alternative:
  ```scss
  // ✅ Acceptable custom focus ring
  &:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--interactive-primary);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  // ❌ Never do this
  &:focus { outline: none; }
  ```

### Interactive Custom Elements
When building non-native interactive elements, add keyboard handlers:
```jsx
// ✅ Custom clickable element with keyboard support
<div
  role="button"
  tabIndex={0}
  onClick={handleClick}
  onKeyDown={(e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
      e.preventDefault();
      handleClick();
    }
  }}
>
  Click me
</div>
```

