## 3. Semantic HTML & ARIA (WCAG 1.3.1 / 4.1.2)

### Use Semantic HTML First
Prefer native HTML elements over ARIA. Native elements have built-in accessibility:
```jsx
// ✅ Native button - keyboard, role, and focus built in
<button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>

// ❌ Avoid - requires manual ARIA + keyboard handling
<div onClick={handleClick}>Submit</div>
```

### Heading Hierarchy
- Use a **single `<h1>`** per page (the page title)
- Headings must follow a logical hierarchy: `h1 → h2 → h3 → h4` — never skip levels
- Use Carbon's `Heading` component (not raw `<h2>`, `<h3>`, etc.):
  ```jsx
  // ✅ Carbon Heading
  import { Heading } from '@carbon/react';
  <Heading as="h2" className="section-title">Features</Heading>

  // ❌ Raw HTML heading (bypasses Carbon's typography system)
  <h2 className="section-title">Features</h2>
  ```

### Lists
Use Carbon's list components instead of raw HTML:
```jsx
// ✅ Carbon list components
import { UnorderedList, ListItem } from '@carbon/react';
<UnorderedList>
  <ListItem>Item one</ListItem>
  <ListItem>Item two</ListItem>
</UnorderedList>

// ❌ Raw HTML (misses Carbon theming + spacing)
<ul><li>Item one</li></ul>
```

### Landmarks
Every page must have these landmark regions:
- `<header>` or `role="banner"` — page header
- `<main>` or `role="main"` — primary content (one per page)
- `<nav>` or `role="navigation"` — navigation menus (with `aria-label` when multiple)
- `<footer>` or `role="contentinfo"` — page footer

