## 4. Images & Icons (WCAG 1.1.1)

### Images
- **Informative images**: must have a descriptive `alt` attribute
  ```jsx
  <img src="car.jpg" alt="Red sedan on a highway representing auto insurance coverage" />
  ```
- **Decorative images**: use `alt=""` to hide from screen readers
  ```jsx
  <img src="divider.svg" alt="" />
  ```
- **Never** omit `alt` entirely (causes screen readers to read the filename)

### Icons
- **Decorative icons** (accompanied by visible text): add `aria-hidden="true"`
  ```jsx
  // ✅ Icon is decorative - label comes from button text
  <Button renderIcon={ArrowRight}>Next</Button>

  // ✅ Standalone icon with no text - needs a label
  <IconButton label="Close dialog" kind="ghost">
    <Close />
  </IconButton>
  ```
- **Standalone icons** (no adjacent text): use `aria-label` on the parent or Carbon's `IconButton`:
  ```jsx
  import { IconButton } from '@carbon/react';
  <IconButton label="Search" kind="ghost"><Search /></IconButton>
  ```

---

## 5. Forms (WCAG 1.3.1 / 3.3.1 / 3.3.2)

### Labels
- **Every form input must have a visible label** — never use placeholder text as the only label
- Use Carbon form components which wire labels automatically:
  ```jsx
  // ✅ Carbon TextInput - label is linked via htmlFor/id
  <TextInput id="email" labelText="Email Address" placeholder="you@example.com" />

  // ❌ Input with no label - inaccessible
  <input type="email" placeholder="Email Address" />
  ```

### Error States
- Use Carbon's built-in `invalid` and `invalidText` props to communicate errors
- Error messages must appear near the field and be announced by screen readers:
  ```jsx
  <TextInput
    id="email"
    labelText="Email Address"
    invalid={emailError}
    invalidText="Please enter a valid email address"
  />
  ```

### Required Fields
- Mark required fields with `required` attribute (Carbon exposes this via props)
- Do not rely solely on color or an asterisk to indicate required fields — include text or `aria-required`

### Helper Text
- Use `helperText` prop on Carbon inputs for additional context (e.g., format hints):
  ```jsx
  <TextInput
    id="vin"
    labelText="VIN (optional)"
    helperText="17 alphanumeric characters"
  />
  ```

### Groups
- Radio buttons and checkboxes must be grouped using `fieldset` + `legend`, or Carbon's `RadioButtonGroup`:
  ```jsx
  import { RadioButtonGroup, RadioButton } from '@carbon/react';
  <RadioButtonGroup legendText="Insurance type" name="insurance-type">
    <RadioButton labelText="Car" value="car" id="car" />
    <RadioButton labelText="Home" value="home" id="home" />
  </RadioButtonGroup>
  ```

