## 6. Modals & Dialogs (WCAG 2.4.3 / 2.1.2)

- Use Carbon's `Modal` or `ComposedModal` — never build custom modal dialogs from scratch
- Focus must move to the dialog when it opens
- Focus must be **trapped** inside the dialog while open (Carbon handles this automatically)
- Focus must return to the trigger element when the dialog closes
- `Escape` key must close the dialog
- Dialog must have an accessible name (`aria-label` or `aria-labelledby`):
  ```jsx
  <Modal
    open={isOpen}
    modalHeading="Request a Demo"   // automatically sets aria-labelledby
    onRequestClose={handleClose}
    primaryButtonText="Submit"
    secondaryButtonText="Cancel"
  >
    {/* content */}
  </Modal>
  ```

---

## 7. Multi-Step Flows (WCAG 2.4.3 / 4.1.3)

- Progress indicators must announce current step to screen readers
- The `StepBreadcrumb` component (`src/components/StepBreadcrumb.jsx`) must include `aria` attributes:
  ```jsx
  // ✅ Step breadcrumb with ARIA (step container)
  <nav aria-label="Progress" role="navigation">
    <ol>
      <li aria-current="step">Step 1: Personal Info</li>
      <li>Step 2: Address</li>
    </ol>
  </nav>
  ```
- When navigating between steps, scroll to the top and move focus to the step heading or a skip link
- Use `aria-live="polite"` regions to announce step transitions:
  ```jsx
  <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" className="sr-only">
    {`Step ${currentStep + 1} of ${totalSteps}: ${stepTitle}`}
  </div>
  ```

---

## 8. Motion & Animation (WCAG 2.3.3)

- Respect the user's `prefers-reduced-motion` media query for all animations and transitions:
  ```scss
  .animated-element {
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;

    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
  ```
- Never auto-play video or audio without user control
- Avoid content that flashes more than 3 times per second

---

## 9. Screen Reader Only Content

Use this utility class (add to `src/styles/index.scss` if not present) for content visible only to screen readers:
```scss
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border-width: 0;
}
```

Use it for supplemental context:
```jsx
<button onClick={handleDelete}>
  Delete
  <span className="sr-only">policy for John Smith</span>
</button>
```

