## 10. Testing Checklist

Before marking any component or page as complete:

### Automated
- [ ] Run browser DevTools Lighthouse audit (target: Accessibility score ≥ 90)
- [ ] Check contrast ratios in DevTools (Elements → Accessibility → Contrast)

### Manual Keyboard
- [ ] Tab through all interactive elements — nothing is skipped
- [ ] Shift+Tab works in reverse
- [ ] Enter/Space activates buttons and controls
- [ ] Escape closes modals and dropdowns
- [ ] Arrow keys work in radio groups, dropdowns, tabs

### Manual Screen Reader (basic)
- [ ] Test with macOS VoiceOver (Cmd+F5) or Windows NVDA
- [ ] All form inputs announce their label when focused
- [ ] Error messages are announced
- [ ] Page/section headings are read in logical order
- [ ] Images have appropriate alt text
- [ ] Decorative icons are silent

### Visual
- [ ] All text has sufficient contrast in light mode
- [ ] All text has sufficient contrast in dark mode
- [ ] Focus rings are visible on every interactive element
- [ ] Page is usable at 200% browser zoom
- [ ] No content is lost when text size is increased

---

## Carbon Design System Accessibility Notes

- Carbon components are accessible **by default** — do not remove or override ARIA attributes without a replacement
- When Carbon components have theming contrast issues (e.g., dark text on dark background in dark mode), fix with high-specificity CSS overrides using theme tokens — see `.builder/rules/theme-contrast-guidelines.mdc`
- The `StepBreadcrumb` custom component replaced Carbon's `ProgressIndicator` due to theming/accessibility issues — see `.builder/rules/banned-components.mdc`
- Always use Carbon's `size`, `kind`, `invalid`, `warn`, and `disabled` props to communicate state — these automatically update ARIA attributes

